Implement the following plan:

# Plan: Fix IntroSlide Pre-Activated Tool Icons

## Context

The IntroSlide ("let's get to know you") shows AI tool icons that should only light up when the user explicitly types a tool name. Instead, icons appear randomly pre-activated whenever the user navigates to the slide. This is confusing for presenters.

**Root cause:** Two bugs in `Presentation.tsx`:

1. **`getMatchingToolIds` runs on commands from every slide**, not just the IntroSlide. Navigation shortcuts like `"n"` (next) match tool keywords via `kw.includes(normalizedInput)` — e.g. `"n"` is contained in `"anthropic"`, `"openai"`, `"gemini"`, `"sourcegraph"`, `"github copilot"`, `"something"` — activating claude, codex, amp, gemini, copilot, ??? all at once. This matches exactly the screenshot.

2. **`activatedTools` is never cleared on slide navigation**, so once polluted, tools stay lit whenever the IntroSlide is visited.

## Critical File

- `src/components/Presentation.tsx` — the only file that needs changes

## Implementation

### Fix 1 — Gate tool activation to the IntroSlide only

In `handleCommand`, wrap the `getMatchingToolIds` call with a guard:

```ts
// Only activate tools when on the IntroSlide
if (slides[currentSlide]?.id === 'intro') {
  const matchingTools = getMatchingToolIds(command);
  if (matchingTools.length > 0) {
    setActivatedTools(prev => {
      const next = new Set(prev);
      matchingTools.forEach(id => next.add(id));
      return next;
    });
  }
}
```

### Fix 2 — Reset activatedTools when navigating to IntroSlide

In the existing `useEffect` that resets `slideInteracted` on slide change, also reset `activatedTools` when landing on the intro slide:

```ts
useEffect(() => {
  setSlideInteracted(false);
  if (slides[currentSlide]?.id === 'intro') {
    setActivatedTools(new Set());
  }
}, [currentSlide]);
```

This ensures each time the presenter arrives at the slide, it starts clean.

## Verification

1. Navigate to the IntroSlide — all icons should be unlit
2. Navigate away (type `n`) and back — icons should still be unlit
3. On the IntroSlide, type `claude` + Enter — only Claude Code highlights
4. Navigate away and back — icons reset to unlit again
5. On a non-IntroSlide, type `gemini` + Enter — no tools activate; navigate to IntroSlide — still all unlit


